@ENDNODE
@NODE whatcanido? "BirdBase Help: What can I do with this program?"

The main features of BirdBase are:

@{fg highlight}Species Database@{fg text}
· Complete species database of British birds
· Systematic order of Voous with English names
@{fg highlight}Sites Database@{fg text}
· Maintain a database of sites and counties
· Sites database is fully editable
@{fg highlight}Recording Sightings@{fg text}
· Sightings are entered from a species list
· Entries are checked against the species and sites databases 
· For each field trip you can record the date, time, weather, site and notes
· For each sighting you can record the species, number, age and sex        
@{fg highlight}Creating Reports@{fg text}
· Create reports by site, county, date, year or species
· Reports can be output to ascii files or directly to other programs
· Reports count the number of species in each list
· Reports also list all individual sightings of each species
· Keep pre-defined lists for quick listing
· Automatic updating of lists
· New lists can be set up at any time
@{fg highlight}Other Features@{fg text}
· Complete on-line Help
@ENDNODE
@NODE tellmeabout "BirdBase Help: Tell me about..."

   @{" The Sites Database               " LINK "sitesdatabase"}
   @{" The Field-trips Database         " LINK "fieldtripsdatabase"} 
   @{" The Lists Database               " LINK "listsdatabase"} 
   @{" The Species Database             " LINK "speciesdatabase"} 

@ENDNODE
@NODE sitesdatabase "BirdBase Help: The Sites Database"

The sites database holds data on the sites you have visited. You can enter
the site and county.

@ENDNODE
@NODE fieldtripsdatabase "BirdBase Help: The Field-trips Database"

The field-trips database holds data on the trips you have been on. For each
field-trip you can enter the date, time, site, weather and notes about the
visit.

@ENDNODE
@NODE listsdatabase "BirdBase Help: The Lists Database"

This table holds your lists. Lists are summaries of your individual
sightings. Lists are basically pre-defined reports and as such can be
defined for dates, years, sites, counties and species.

@ENDNODE
@NODE speciesdatabase "BirdBase Help: The Species Database"

BirdBase comes with a complete list of British birds. It follows the order
of Voous (1977) and is the standard order in which birds are listed in most
field guides.

@ENDNODE
