@NODE addfieldtrip "BirdBase Help: Adding a new Field-trip"
 @{fg highlight}Adding a new Field-trip@{fg text}@{B}
 
 1. Select NEW FIELD-TRIP from the CREATE menu or press Amiga-F.@{UB}

    Today's date will be automatically entered into the date text box but
    you can change it if you wish.@{B}
 
 2. Enter the trip details into the text boxes.@{UB}

    The only text boxes which are compulsary are the date and site. The site
    must match one of your sites in the Sites database. If it doesn't a
    requester will warn you.@{B}

 @{fg highlight}Entering sightings to your Field-trip@{fg text}@{UB}

    You will notice that there are two lists. The one on the left holds the
    complete species database and the one on the right holds the list of
    species for the current Field-trip.@{B}

 1. Select one of the species from the Species List.@{UB}

    The bird you have just selected will then appear on the Trip List.@{B}

 2. Repeat step 1 untill you have added all the sightings for the trip and
    then click on OK. 
@ENDNODE
@NODE addlist "BirdBase Help: Adding a new list"
 @{fg highlight}Adding a new list@{fg text}@{B}
 
 1. Select NEW LIST from the CREATE menu or press Amiga-L.@{UB}

    A requester will come up from which you can define the list.@{B}

 2. Enter the list name and search criteria and click on OK.@{UB}

    The list requester is identical to the report requester but you must
    make sure you enter a name for the list.
@ENDNODE
@NODE addsite "BirdBase Help: Adding a new site"
 @{fg highlight}Adding a new site@{fg text}@{B}
 
 1. Select NEW SITE from the CREATE menu or press Amiga-T.@{UB}

    A requester will come up from which you can enter the site details.@{B}

 2. Enter the site details and click on OK.
@ENDNODE
@NODE createnewfile "BirdBase Help: Creating new files"
 @{fg highlight}Creating new files@{fg text}@{B}

 1. Select NEW from the PROJECT menu or press Amiga-N.@{UB}

    All the current data will be wiped from memory allowing you to create
    completely new sites and trip databases.
@ENDNODE
@NODE createreports "BirdBase Help: Creating Reports"
 @{fg highlight}Creating Reports@{fg text}@{B}

 1. Select CREATE REPORT from the REPORT menu.@{UB}

    The report requester will come up from which you can enter the search
    criteria.@{B}

 2. Enter the search criteria and click on OK.@{UB}

    You can enter a name for the report if you wish but if you don't the
    search criteria will be used as the name.@{B}
@ENDNODE
@NODE deletetrip "BirdBase Help: Deleting Field-Trips"
 @{fg highlight}Deleting Field-trips@{fg text}@{B}

 1. Select FIELD-TRIPS from the WINDOWS menu.@{UB}

    A window will come up with a list of all of your field-trips.@{B}

 2. Select the trip you wish to delete and click on the DELETE button.@{UB}
@ENDNODE
@NODE deletelist "BirdBase Help: Deleting Lists"
 @{fg highlight}Deleting lists@{fg text}@{B}

 1. Select LISTS from the WINDOWS menu.@{UB}

    A window will come up with a list of all of your lists.@{B}

 2. Select the list you wish to delete and click on the DELETE button.@{UB}
@ENDNODE
@NODE deletesite "BirdBase Help: Deleting Sites"
 @{fg highlight}Deleting Sites@{fg text}@{B}

 1. Select SITES from the WINDOWS menu.@{UB}

    A window will come up with a list of all of your sites.@{B}

 2. Select the site you wish to delete and click on the DELETE button.@{UB}
@ENDNODE
@NODE editfieldtrip "BirdBase Help: Editing Field-trips"
 @{fg highlight}Editing Field-trips@{fg text}@{B}

 1. Select FIELD-TRIPS from the WINDOWS menu.@{UB}

    A window will come up with a list of all of your field-trips.@{B}

 2. Select the field-trip you wish to edit and click on the EDIT button.@{UB}

    The field-trip requester which you used to enter the trip details will
    come up.@{B}

 3. Enter the new field-trip details and click on OK.
@ENDNODE
@NODE editlist "BirdBase Help: Editing lists"
 @{fg highlight}Editing lists@{fg text}@{B}

 1. Select LISTS from the WINDOWS menu.@{UB}

    A window will come up with a list of all of your lists.@{B}

 2. Select the list you wish to edit and click on the EDIT button.@{UB}

    The list requester which you used to enter the trip details will come
    up.@{B}

 3. Enter the new list details and click on OK.
@ENDNODE
@NODE editsite "BirdBase Help: Editing sites"
 @{fg highlight}Editing sites@{fg text}@{B}

 1. Select SITES from the WINDOWS menu.@{UB}

    A window will come up with a list of all of your sites.@{B}

 2. Select the site you wish to edit and click on the EDIT button.@{UB}

    The site requester which you used to enter the site details will come
    up.@{B}

 3. Enter the new site details and click on OK.
@ENDNODE
@NODE enterrecords "BirdBase Help: Entering sighting records"
 @{fg highlight}Entering sighting records@{fg text}@{UB}
 
 It is possible to enter details of numbers seen, age and sex. These can be
 entered while you are creating the filed-trip or added at a later date. To
 add record details make sure you are on the field-trip edit window.@{B}

 1. Select the sighting you want to add details to from the trip list.@{UB}

    There are two buttons on the right of the window - Edit and Delete.
    When you click on a sighting these buttons will become enabled.@{B}

 2. Click on the EDIT button.@{UB}

    The record requester will come up from which you can enter details of
    number seen, age and sex.@{B}

 3. Enter the record details and click on OK.
@ENDNODE
@NODE importreport "BirdBase Help: Importing reports"
 @{fg highlight}Importing reports@{fg text}@{B}

 Select WORD PROCESSOR from the OUTPUT sub-menu on the REPORT
 menu.
@ENDNODE
@NODE openfile "BirdBase Help: Opening files"
 @{fg highlight}Opening files@{fg text}@{B}
 
 1. Select OPEN from the PROJECT menu or press Amiga-O.@{UB}

    A file requester will come up.@{B}

 2. Select the file you want to open and click on OK.
@ENDNODE
@NODE print "BirdBase Help: Printing"
 @{fg highlight}Printing@{fg text}@{B}
 
 1. Make sure your printer is on-line.

 2. Select PRINT REPORT from the REPORT menu.
@ENDNODE
@NODE quit "BirdBase Help: Quiting BirdBase"
 @{fg highlight}Quiting BirdBase@{fg text}@{B}
 
 1. Select QUIT from the PROJECT menu or press Amiga-Q.@{UB}

    A requester will come up asking whether you are sure.@{B}

 2. Click on YES or NO.
@ENDNODE
@NODE savefile "BirdBase Help: Saving files"
 @{fg highlight}Saving files@{fg text}@{B}
 
 1. Select SAVE from the PROJECT menu or press Amiga-S.@{UB}

    The Save option will be disabled if you have not already saved your
    file with the Save As option. Save will just re-save the file under the
    current name.
@ENDNODE
@NODE savefileas "BirdBase Help: Saving files as different names"
 @{fg highlight}Saving files as different names@{fg text}@{B}
 
 1. Select SAVE AS from the PROJECT menu or press Amiga-A.@{UB}

    A file requester will come up.@{B}

 2. Enter the name and path of the file and click on OK.
@ENDNODE
@NODE savereport "BirdBase Help: Saving reports"
 @{fg highlight}Saving reports@{fg text}@{B}
 
 1. Select ASCII FILE from the OUTPUT sub-menu on the REPORT menu.@{UB}

    A file requester will come up.@{B}

 2. Enter the name and path of the file and click on OK.
@ENDNODE
@NODE setword "BirdBase Help: Setting the Word Processor"
 @{fg highlight}Setting the Word Processor@{fg text}
 
 The path of the Word Processor to be used for outputting reports to is set
 by using tool types. If you don't know what tool types are look in the
 relevant section of your WorkBench manual. Here is a quick run down on how
 to set tool types.@{B}

 1. Click on the BirdBase icon.

 2. Select INFORMATION from the ICONS window or press Amiga-I.@{UB}

    A requester will come up showing information on the icon.@{B}

 3. Click on the NEW button and type "WORD=<path of your Word Processor>"
    and click on OK.@{UB}

    For example: WORD=DH1:APPS/FINALWITER/FINALWRITER
@ENDNODE
@NODE viewlist "BirdBase Help: Viewing lists"
 @{fg highlight}Viewing lists@{fg text}@{B}
 
 1. Select LISTS from the WINDOWS menu.@{UB}

    A window will come up with a list of all your lists.@{B}

 2. Select the list you wish to view.@{UB}

    There are a number of buttons on the right of the window. When you click
    on a list these buttons will become enabled.@{B}

 3. Click on the VIEW button.
@ENDNODE
@NODE hintsandtips "BirdBase Help: Hints and Tips"

@{B}How can I speed up my reports?@{UB}
Create a new file for each year. This will keep the size of your files down
to a minimum and will also keep the speed at which reports are created to
an acceptable speed. Alternatively buy an accelerator. An 030 can make a lot
of difference.

@{B}How can I enter different sites for one trip?@{UB}
If you want your reports to be more accurate for individual sites then
create a new field-trip for each site visited during the day. If you are
not too bothered about your site reports then you could create a site
called something like "North Norfolk Coast" and use one field-trip for a
day on the North Norfolk Coast.

@{B}How detailed do the records have to be?@{UB}
This is really up to you. To get the most complete set of records you must
create a new field-trip for each site you visit during the day. If you
want every sighting to be recorded you would have to enter all the birds
you see at each site. So, for instance, if you saw a Blackbird at Cley in
the morning and then again in the afternoon at Titchwell, you would enter
two records for Blackbird. In practice this is a lot of effort. A good
compromise is to enter a record for the first sighting only. So, enter all
your records for Cley and then add any additional species you see at
Titchwell.
@ENDNODE
